Package: margot.sim
Type: Package
Title: Simulate Longitudinal Data with Observational Shadows and Monte Carlo Evaluation
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: 
    person("Joseph", "Bulbulia", email = "joseph.bulbulia@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5861-2056"))
Description: Extensions to the margot package for simulating longitudinal data 
    using Structural Causal Models (SCMs). Provides sophisticated capabilities 
    for applying various observational shadows (measurement error, missingness, 
    selection bias) to simulated data, running Monte Carlo simulations to evaluate 
    statistical estimators, supporting flexible non-normal distributions, and creating 
    a unified framework for causal inference method evaluation.
